      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That makes sense, I get that it was all pseudoscience. But for my paper, I really need to deconstruct the actual logic they used to make it sound convincing at the time. Like, what were the specific \"scientific\" metrics or observations they pointed to? For example, how did they use things like cranial measurements or IQ-style testing to categorize groups into these hierarchies? I want to be able to cite the specific ways they tried to \"prove\" these differences.",
